metadata.name: Fractured Spectra v1.9 #22
metadata.description:
My continued exploration of color, shape, form, function, fractal chaos, order, and understanding of the mathematical beauty of nature to create beautiful, unique and colorful designs made up of translucent glassy elements. In this piece I explore symmetry and contrasting elements, suggesting a nearly impossible blown glass sculpture. Each unique rendering has a character of its own, some smooth and sensuous while others with sharp color and form changes, ragged edges, and chaotic beauty. Interactive with several user controls:

With the mouse:

Left click and drag to change the viewing angle
Right click and drag to change the view center
Mouse wheel to change the distance to the view center

With the keyboard:

Keys "," and "." (i.e. "<" and ">") change the rotation speed left or right. You can stop it entirely, or speed it up to what I consider a reasonable maximum, rotating to the left or to the right. Each time you press, it adjusts the rotation speed

Keys "a" "b" and "c": the lights always start in the same place, and each key controls one of the three lights, both position and intensity. It is deterministic from the initial start based upon the token: for a given token, after the initial run (or re-run) pressing "aaabbcabcabc" will give you the same sequence of lighting changes. This lets you choose your favorite and keep track of it.

metadata.name: Leviathan #191
metadata.description:
Leviathan is a generative collection of large bodies made form particles, materialised from the viewers own subconscious. Atoms form gargantuan objects - subatomic monoliths and microscopic giants. Playing with the sense of scale it draws on the viewer‚Äôs subjective way of associating forms, a pattern that becomes a mirror, a skeleton for them to project. 

Part artist, part viewer. Leviathan asks us to question these relationships of creation, ownership and meaning. It is a chemical reaction that the artist starts and you finish. A colossal dream we are all sharing together - a leviathan.

metadata.name: Chance #124
metadata.description:
The world is chaotic at first glance. Throwing a die, trading stocks or cryptocurrencies, or simply walking through a crowded city center can have unpredictable outcomes.

Computers are different. Algorithms are deterministic by design. Given the same input, they always produce the same result. In reverse, it‚Äôs impossible for a computer to produce a string that is truly unpredictable. What is usually an advantage becomes a problem in cryptography.

To provide truly random numbers for encryption, Silicon Graphics filed a patent in 1996 for Lavarand. By taking photos of a bunch of physical lava lamps, they generated the random numbers needed for privacy and security in the computer age. While the original patent expired, the most important internet infrastructure provider, Cloudflare*, built their own lava lamp wall in their San Francisco headquarters. They are used to provide SSL/TLS encryption to their customers.

Chance turns the Lavarand concept on its head. It generates a simulated lava lamp from the unique seed that is stored in each generative NFT. The ThreeJS simulation runs in the browser. Unlike the physical lava lamps, their movements are determined because they follow mathematical calculations that always produce the same movements and shapes. Under which conditions could the simulation become as complex as the physical lamps?

Thank you to the three.js community and the creators of the Marching Cubes example (greggman, Henrik Rydg√•rd). Optimized for Chrome version 105.


*according to Forbes ‚ÄúHow Cloudflare Became The Most Important Internet Company Nobody Has Heard Of‚Äù (Dec 4, 2020)

metadata.name: The Manuscript #33
metadata.description:
This unique collection of generative art that explores the mysteries of alien languages and ancient manuscripts. These works tell stories that we may or may not be able to understand fully, inviting the viewer to ponder the unknown and the possibility of other forms of communication and expression. The collection combines the ancient and the futuristic, using digital techniques to create abstract and surreal representations of these mysterious texts. The result is a captivating and thought-provoking collection that pushes the boundaries of contemporary art. Each piece is unique and evocative, inviting the viewer to get lost in the beauty of the unknown and to consider the possibilities of other worlds and other ways of communicating.

In this collection, the use of generative art techniques adds an element of randomness and unpredictability, mirroring the mysterious nature of the alien scripts and ancient manuscripts. The pieces are created through a combination of algorithms and human input, resulting in a dynamic interplay between the programmed and the organic. The viewer is invited to experience the art as an ever-evolving representation of the unknown. The glitches and digital distortions in the art add a sense of chaos and unpredictability, inviting the viewer to ponder the possibilities of other forms of communication and expression. The collection pushes the boundaries of contemporary art and invites the viewer to engage with the mystery of the unknown.

Press [S] to save a PNG image.

Genuary 2023: Typography

metadata.description:
Welcome to Arizona!
I have turned Arizona into a work of art in my own style
Play with lines, colors, plants, mountains and rocks
It was an interesting event for me in the style of the Arizona desert zoo
I hope you enjoy watching it too



This collection is the result of my playing with the lines I drew with the tablet.
This collection has 11 layers
The first layer contains the background
The second and third layer of ground and background lines
The fourth layer of mountains and rocks contains 21 images in zentangle style
The fifth layer of stones and rocks
The sixth layer of cacti
The next layers are rocks and deserts and flowers and plants
11th signature layer

metadata.name: aether:Astral Loom #40
metadata.description:
Weaving on the astral plane. Lines of transmission. 
Some journeys are straightforward, others yield a multitude of pathways.
Disconnect to interpret.

(As an experiment) the rarity values assigned to this artwork are completely arbitrary, and are in no way connected to the visual output of the minted piece. One might wonder, why have rarity values at all? That's what I ask myself any time I see a value based on rarity attributes instead of viewer aesthetic. 

That being said, I suppose it's up to each person to decide for themselves the value of art...

This artwork was created using p5js.

metadata.name: Alleles #341
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Exploration of available data indicates that suggests subject may be succeptible to frequent periods of anxiety and negative internal dialogue, yet also displays a rare level of interpersonal connection and leadership. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 125-134cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 92-102 years.
